headline: Mums the Word (and the organiser): OpenTable research reveals 50% of mums have booked their own Mother's Day meal out
summary: Mother's Day is a time for mums and mother figures to relax – but for many, it appears that this may not be the case. New research from OpenTable has revealed that half of UK mothers (50%) have booked their own celebratory Mother's Day meal.*

headline: Agoda Highlights 5 Alternative Destinations to Celebrate Songkran Beyond Bangkok
summary: With mid-April fast approaching, Thailand is getting ready to celebrate the new year festival of Songkran. In Bangkok, iconic locations such as Khao San Road and Silom Road are often the go-to spots for the celebrations that always mean getting soaking wet. This year, digital travel platform Agoda shares five alternative destinations across Thailand for travelers seeking fresh ways to enjoy Songkran and explore beyond the capital.
